<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="111" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,310,906,932]" box="[189,310,906,932]" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,906,932]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="111" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,906,932]" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1399,952,1049]" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">Seven outer paleae cylindrical at base, flattened sharp tips, and serrate margins. Four inner paleae cylindrical, blunt tips and faintly serrate margins. Median organ shorter than lobes, cylindrical, without lateral eyespots, with truncate and pigmented tip.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="111" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,324,1088,1114]" box="[189,324,1088,1114]" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1088,1114]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="111" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1088,1114]" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[188,1399,1135,1231]" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">
This species name is after Dr Daniel 
<collectingCountry box="[626,753,1135,1161]" name="Guadeloupe" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">Guadalupe</collectingCountry>
Pech Pool, head of the BIOMARCCA collection, who kindly lent me the 
<typeStatus box="[407,510,1170,1196]" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen. The species name is a noun in the genitive case (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[1204,1342,1170,1196]" pageId="2" pageNumber="111" refId="ref15146" refString="ICZN (International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature). 1999. International Code of Zoological Nomenclature, 4 th Ed. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, The Natural History Museum, London. Available from https: // www. iczn. org / the-code / the-code-online / [accessed 31 Jan. 2022]." type="url" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
, Art. 31.1.2).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
