<paragraph blockId="2.[189,334,1453,1479]" box="[189,334,1453,1479]" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,1453,1479]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="111" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,1453,1479]" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[188,1398,1499,1562]" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">
<collectionCode box="[189,254,1500,1526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">BODY</collectionCode>
. 
<typeStatus box="[268,377,1499,1525]" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">Holotype</typeStatus>
complete (ECOSUR-302), preserved material colorless, 
<quantity box="[1041,1131,1499,1526]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="111" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1203,1292,1500,1526]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="111" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
wide, 17 abdominal segments, caudal peduncle 
<quantity box="[640,730,1535,1562]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="111" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation box="[805,874,1535,1561]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1816,1842]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-11@3.[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Lygdamis pechi sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-302). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B–C. Anterior region, dorsal view. D. Median ridge and median organ, ventral view. E. Thorax and parathoracic region, ventral view.F. Posterior region, dorsal view.Abbreviations: c1t = cirrus 1st thoracic segment; mo = median organ; mr = median ridge; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; nh = nuchal hooks; no = parathoracic notopod; opa = opercular papillae; pa = palps; tf = tentacular filament. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885278/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[187,1400,1600,1944]" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">
OPERCULUM. Opercular disc oblique, two rows of translucent, pale yellow paleae; outer row with 6–7 paleae per lobe, inner row with four paleae per lobe (
<figureCitation box="[818,948,1635,1661]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1816,1842]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-11@3.[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Lygdamis pechi sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-302). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B–C. Anterior region, dorsal view. D. Median ridge and median organ, ventral view. E. Thorax and parathoracic region, ventral view.F. Posterior region, dorsal view.Abbreviations: c1t = cirrus 1st thoracic segment; mo = median organ; mr = median ridge; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; nh = nuchal hooks; no = parathoracic notopod; opa = opercular papillae; pa = palps; tf = tentacular filament. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885278/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">Fig. 1A–C</figureCitation>
). Outer paleae cylindrical at base with flattened, sharp tip; blade straight with serrated margins (
<figureCitation box="[880,1012,1670,1697]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1886,1912]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,267,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-12@4.[189,1398,267,1836]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Lygdamis pechi sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-302).A. Opercular paleae.B. Outer paleae.C. Detail of the outer paleae tips. D. Inner palea. E. Parathoracic notochaetae. F. Parathoracic neurochaetae. G. Abdominal uncini. Abbreviations: op = outer paleae; ip = inner paleae. Numbers indicate the rows of teeth. Scale bars: A–B = 100 µm; C = 20 µm; D–F = 50 µm; G = 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885280" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885280/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">Fig. 2A–C</figureCitation>
). Inner paleae 1.6 times as long as outer paleae, cylindrical; blade straight, with faintly serrate margins and blunt tips (
<figureCitation box="[1247,1385,1706,1732]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1886,1912]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,267,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-12@4.[189,1398,267,1836]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Lygdamis pechi sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-302).A. Opercular paleae.B. Outer paleae.C. Detail of the outer paleae tips. D. Inner palea. E. Parathoracic notochaetae. F. Parathoracic neurochaetae. G. Abdominal uncini. Abbreviations: op = outer paleae; ip = inner paleae. Numbers indicate the rows of teeth. Scale bars: A–B = 100 µm; C = 20 µm; D–F = 50 µm; G = 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885280" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885280/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">Fig. 2A, D</figureCitation>
). Opercular stalk twice longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[682,815,1741,1767]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1816,1842]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-11@3.[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Lygdamis pechi sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-302). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B–C. Anterior region, dorsal view. D. Median ridge and median organ, ventral view. E. Thorax and parathoracic region, ventral view.F. Posterior region, dorsal view.Abbreviations: c1t = cirrus 1st thoracic segment; mo = median organ; mr = median ridge; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; nh = nuchal hooks; no = parathoracic notopod; opa = opercular papillae; pa = palps; tf = tentacular filament. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885278/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">Fig. 1A–B</figureCitation>
). Five to six opercular papillae decrease in size ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[312,406,1776,1802]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1816,1842]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-11@3.[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Lygdamis pechi sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-302). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B–C. Anterior region, dorsal view. D. Median ridge and median organ, ventral view. E. Thorax and parathoracic region, ventral view.F. Posterior region, dorsal view.Abbreviations: c1t = cirrus 1st thoracic segment; mo = median organ; mr = median ridge; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; nh = nuchal hooks; no = parathoracic notopod; opa = opercular papillae; pa = palps; tf = tentacular filament. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885278/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
); first pair of papillae about four times as long as others, with dark tips (
<figureCitation box="[1290,1383,1776,1802]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1816,1842]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-11@3.[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Lygdamis pechi sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-302). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B–C. Anterior region, dorsal view. D. Median ridge and median organ, ventral view. E. Thorax and parathoracic region, ventral view.F. Posterior region, dorsal view.Abbreviations: c1t = cirrus 1st thoracic segment; mo = median organ; mr = median ridge; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; nh = nuchal hooks; no = parathoracic notopod; opa = opercular papillae; pa = palps; tf = tentacular filament. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885278/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Nine rows of buccal tentacles. Palps slightly longer than median organ, as long as opercular stalk lobes (
<figureCitation box="[198,289,1846,1873]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1816,1842]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-11@3.[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Lygdamis pechi sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-302). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B–C. Anterior region, dorsal view. D. Median ridge and median organ, ventral view. E. Thorax and parathoracic region, ventral view.F. Posterior region, dorsal view.Abbreviations: c1t = cirrus 1st thoracic segment; mo = median organ; mr = median ridge; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; nh = nuchal hooks; no = parathoracic notopod; opa = opercular papillae; pa = palps; tf = tentacular filament. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885278/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). A pair of nuchal hooks, large, sharp (
<figureCitation box="[726,850,1846,1873]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1816,1842]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-11@3.[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Lygdamis pechi sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-302). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B–C. Anterior region, dorsal view. D. Median ridge and median organ, ventral view. E. Thorax and parathoracic region, ventral view.F. Posterior region, dorsal view.Abbreviations: c1t = cirrus 1st thoracic segment; mo = median organ; mr = median ridge; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; nh = nuchal hooks; no = parathoracic notopod; opa = opercular papillae; pa = palps; tf = tentacular filament. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885278/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">Fig. 1B–C</figureCitation>
). Median ridge with marginal eyespots. Median organ shorter than lobes, almost four times as long as wide, cylindrical, tip truncate and pigmented, without lateral eyespots (
<figureCitation box="[484,577,1917,1943]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1816,1842]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-11@3.[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Lygdamis pechi sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-302). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B–C. Anterior region, dorsal view. D. Median ridge and median organ, ventral view. E. Thorax and parathoracic region, ventral view.F. Posterior region, dorsal view.Abbreviations: c1t = cirrus 1st thoracic segment; mo = median organ; mr = median ridge; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; nh = nuchal hooks; no = parathoracic notopod; opa = opercular papillae; pa = palps; tf = tentacular filament. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885278/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="111">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885278" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6885278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885278/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="112" startId="3.[189,232,1816,1842]" targetBox="[189,1398,275,1765]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[187,1399,1816,2019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,275,1816,1842]" pageId="3" pageNumber="112">Fig. 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[290,482,1816,1842]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Lygdamis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="3" pageNumber="112" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pechi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[290,482,1816,1842]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="112">Lygdamis pechi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[496,597,1817,1843]" pageId="3" pageNumber="112" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype (ECOSUR-302). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[944,965,1816,1842]" pageId="3" pageNumber="112">A</emphasis>
. Complete specimen, dorsal view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,244,1851,1877]" pageId="3" pageNumber="112">B–C</emphasis>
. Anterior region, dorsal view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[617,638,1852,1878]" pageId="3" pageNumber="112">D</emphasis>
. Median ridge and median organ, ventral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1224,1244,1852,1878]" pageId="3" pageNumber="112">E</emphasis>
. Thorax and parathoracic region, ventral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[581,599,1887,1913]" pageId="3" pageNumber="112">F</emphasis>
. Posterior region, dorsal view.Abbreviations: c1t = cirrus 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1287,1298,1886,1900]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="112">st</superScript>
thoracic segment; mo = median organ; mr = median ridge; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; nh = nuchal hooks; no = parathoracic notopod; opa = opercular papillae; pa = palps; tf = tentacular filament. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 200 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885280" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6885280" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885280/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113" startId="4.[189,232,1886,1912]" targetBox="[189,1398,267,1836]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[186,1399,1886,2019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,1886,1912]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Fig. 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[269,451,1886,1912]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Lygdamis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="113" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pechi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[269,451,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Lygdamis pechi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[455,545,1887,1913]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype (ECOSUR-302). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[860,881,1886,1912]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">A</emphasis>
. Opercular paleae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1101,1121,1887,1913]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">B</emphasis>
. Outer paleae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1291,1312,1886,1912]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">C</emphasis>
. Detail of the outer paleae tips. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[492,513,1922,1948]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">D</emphasis>
. Inner palea. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[686,706,1922,1948]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">E</emphasis>
. Parathoracic notochaetae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1041,1059,1922,1948]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">F</emphasis>
. Parathoracic neurochaetae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,212,1957,1983]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">G</emphasis>
. Abdominal uncini. Abbreviations: op = outer paleae; ip = inner paleae. Numbers indicate the rows of teeth. Scale bars: A–B = 100 µm; C = 20 µm; D–F = 50 µm; G = 10 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,265,327]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">
THORAX. First thoracic segment with one lobe-shaped neuropodium and capillary chaetae (
<figureCitation box="[1290,1384,265,291]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1816,1842]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-11@3.[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Lygdamis pechi sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-302). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B–C. Anterior region, dorsal view. D. Median ridge and median organ, ventral view. E. Thorax and parathoracic region, ventral view.F. Posterior region, dorsal view.Abbreviations: c1t = cirrus 1st thoracic segment; mo = median organ; mr = median ridge; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; nh = nuchal hooks; no = parathoracic notopod; opa = opercular papillae; pa = palps; tf = tentacular filament. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885278/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Second segment with capillary neurochaetae, two triangular-shaped lateral lobes, and paired branchiae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,366,462]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">
PARATHORAX. With four segments, all with branchiae. Notopodia with six lanceolate and five capillary chaetae (
<figureCitation box="[293,384,401,427]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1886,1912]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,267,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-12@4.[189,1398,267,1836]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Lygdamis pechi sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-302).A. Opercular paleae.B. Outer paleae.C. Detail of the outer paleae tips. D. Inner palea. E. Parathoracic notochaetae. F. Parathoracic neurochaetae. G. Abdominal uncini. Abbreviations: op = outer paleae; ip = inner paleae. Numbers indicate the rows of teeth. Scale bars: A–B = 100 µm; C = 20 µm; D–F = 50 µm; G = 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885280" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885280/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
). Neurochaetae with four lanceolate and five capillaries, half the length of notochaetae (
<figureCitation box="[198,287,436,462]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1886,1912]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,267,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-12@4.[189,1398,267,1836]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Lygdamis pechi sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-302).A. Opercular paleae.B. Outer paleae.C. Detail of the outer paleae tips. D. Inner palea. E. Parathoracic notochaetae. F. Parathoracic neurochaetae. G. Abdominal uncini. Abbreviations: op = outer paleae; ip = inner paleae. Numbers indicate the rows of teeth. Scale bars: A–B = 100 µm; C = 20 µm; D–F = 50 µm; G = 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885280" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885280/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[188,1399,501,598]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">
ABDOMEN. Abdominal segments with paired branchiae up to segment 4 (
<figureCitation box="[1078,1212,501,528]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1816,1842]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-11@3.[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Lygdamis pechi sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-302). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B–C. Anterior region, dorsal view. D. Median ridge and median organ, ventral view. E. Thorax and parathoracic region, ventral view.F. Posterior region, dorsal view.Abbreviations: c1t = cirrus 1st thoracic segment; mo = median organ; mr = median ridge; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; nh = nuchal hooks; no = parathoracic notopod; opa = opercular papillae; pa = palps; tf = tentacular filament. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885278/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">Fig. 1A, F</figureCitation>
). Neurochaetae capillary, ornamented with irregular thecal laminar extensions. Notopodia with series of uncini with 6–7 transverse rows of teeth (
<figureCitation box="[483,578,572,598]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1886,1912]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,267,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-12@4.[189,1398,267,1836]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Lygdamis pechi sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-302).A. Opercular paleae.B. Outer paleae.C. Detail of the outer paleae tips. D. Inner palea. E. Parathoracic notochaetae. F. Parathoracic neurochaetae. G. Abdominal uncini. Abbreviations: op = outer paleae; ip = inner paleae. Numbers indicate the rows of teeth. Scale bars: A–B = 100 µm; C = 20 µm; D–F = 50 µm; G = 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885280" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885280/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
). Caudal peduncle colorless, small, cylindrical (
<figureCitation box="[1141,1229,572,598]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1816,1842]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-11@3.[189,1398,275,1765]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Lygdamis pechi sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-302). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B–C. Anterior region, dorsal view. D. Median ridge and median organ, ventral view. E. Thorax and parathoracic region, ventral view.F. Posterior region, dorsal view.Abbreviations: c1t = cirrus 1st thoracic segment; mo = median organ; mr = median ridge; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; nh = nuchal hooks; no = parathoracic notopod; opa = opercular papillae; pa = palps; tf = tentacular filament. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm; B–F = 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885278/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="114" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,303,637,663]" box="[189,303,637,663]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,637,663]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,637,663]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1400,684,957]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">
<bibRefCitation author="Uebelacker J." box="[189,407,684,710]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" refId="ref15317" refString="Uebelacker J. 1984. Chapter 49. Sabellariidae. In: Uebelacker J. M. &amp; Johson P. G. (eds) Taxonomic Guide to the Polychaetes of the Northern Gulf of Mexico. Vol. 7: 49 - 1 - 49 - 10. Barry A. Vittor &amp; Associates, Lousiana, USA." type="book" year="1984">Uebelacker (1984)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName authority="Kinberg, 1867" authorityName="Kinberg" authorityYear="1867" box="[524,905,684,710]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Lygdamis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="indicus">
<emphasis box="[524,729,684,710]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">Lygdamis indicus</emphasis>
Kinberg, 1867
</taxonomicName>
for the west coast of 
<collectingRegion box="[1154,1242,684,710]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">Florida</collectingRegion>
, northeastern Gulf of 
<collectingRegion box="[286,379,719,745]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">Mexico</collectingRegion>
. Her specimens had “14–31 pairs of outer paleae slender, faintly serrate, and distally pointed in juveniles, smooth with tips often bent in adults; …6–16 pairs of inner paleae stouter, blunttipped, smooth in adults, faintly serrate in juveniles; …a median tentacle (or median organ) stout with dark brown tip” (
<bibRefCitation author="Uebelacker J." box="[392,667,824,851]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" refId="ref15317" refString="Uebelacker J. 1984. Chapter 49. Sabellariidae. In: Uebelacker J. M. &amp; Johson P. G. (eds) Taxonomic Guide to the Polychaetes of the Northern Gulf of Mexico. Vol. 7: 49 - 1 - 49 - 10. Barry A. Vittor &amp; Associates, Lousiana, USA." type="book" year="1984">Uebelacker 1984: 49-5</bibRefCitation>
). The faintly serrated outer and inner paleae of specimens that 
<bibRefCitation author="Uebelacker J." box="[189,409,860,886]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" refId="ref15317" refString="Uebelacker J. 1984. Chapter 49. Sabellariidae. In: Uebelacker J. M. &amp; Johson P. G. (eds) Taxonomic Guide to the Polychaetes of the Northern Gulf of Mexico. Vol. 7: 49 - 1 - 49 - 10. Barry A. Vittor &amp; Associates, Lousiana, USA." type="book" year="1984">Uebelacker (1984)</bibRefCitation>
described as juveniles resemble the opercular paleae of 
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[1082,1178,860,886]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Lygdamis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pechi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1082,1178,860,886]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">L. pechi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1186,1278,860,886]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[190,285,895,921]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Lygdamis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pechi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[190,285,895,921]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">L. pechi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[293,384,896,922]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has outer paleae with flattened tips, and fewer opercular paleae (6–7 outer paleae per lobe, four inner paleae per lobe).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,996,1163]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">
<bibRefCitation author="Kirtley D. W." box="[189,358,996,1022]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" refId="ref15203" refString="Kirtley D. W. 1994. A Review and Taxonomic Revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida: Polychaeta). Sabecon Press Science Series, Stuart, Florida." type="book" year="1994">Kirtley (1994)</bibRefCitation>
included some of the Uebelacker’s records in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirtley, 1994" authorityName=", Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[909,1234,996,1022]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Lygdamis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="rayrobertsi">
<emphasis box="[909,1071,996,1022]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">L. rayrobertsi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kirtley D. W." box="[1078,1234,996,1022]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" refId="ref15203" refString="Kirtley D. W. 1994. A Review and Taxonomic Revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida: Polychaeta). Sabecon Press Science Series, Stuart, Florida." type="book" year="1994">Kirtley, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[1306,1395,996,1022]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">Florida</collectingRegion>
. Kirtley also indicated that the record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kinberg" authorityYear="1867" box="[637,750,1031,1057]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Lygdamis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="indicus">
<emphasis box="[637,750,1031,1057]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">L. indicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Gulf of 
<collectingRegion box="[913,1003,1031,1057]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">Mexico</collectingRegion>
was a misidentification. However, he failed to explain any morphological variations of the opercular paleae described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Uebelacker J." pageId="5" pageNumber="114" refId="ref15317" refString="Uebelacker J. 1984. Chapter 49. Sabellariidae. In: Uebelacker J. M. &amp; Johson P. G. (eds) Taxonomic Guide to the Polychaetes of the Northern Gulf of Mexico. Vol. 7: 49 - 1 - 49 - 10. Barry A. Vittor &amp; Associates, Lousiana, USA." type="book" year="1984">Uebelacker (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, so it is not possible to determine whether the juvenile specimen described by Uebelacker also belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[318,480,1136,1162]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Lygdamis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="rayrobertsi">
<emphasis box="[318,480,1136,1162]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">L. rayrobertsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,1202,1334]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">
In the brief description of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Kirtley (1994)" authorityName=", Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[512,866,1202,1228]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Lygdamis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="rayrobertsi">
<emphasis box="[512,677,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">L. rayrobertsi</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirtley D. W." box="[695,866,1202,1228]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" refId="ref15203" refString="Kirtley D. W. 1994. A Review and Taxonomic Revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida: Polychaeta). Sabecon Press Science Series, Stuart, Florida." type="book" year="1994">Kirtley (1994)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
mentioned smooth outer paleae with sharp, slightly bent, conical tips; broad, flat inner paleae with smooth margins; and a median organ ending in discoidal, pigmented, truncate tip. 
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[606,794,1272,1298]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Lygdamis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pechi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[606,794,1272,1298]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">Lygdamis pechi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[803,897,1273,1299]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[959,1124,1272,1298]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Lygdamis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="rayrobertsi">
<emphasis box="[959,1124,1272,1298]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">L. rayrobertsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
share a robust median organ; however, they differ in the morphology of their opercular paleae (see key above).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[187,1400,1373,1540]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">
<bibRefCitation author="Kirtley D. W." box="[189,356,1373,1399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" refId="ref15203" refString="Kirtley D. W. 1994. A Review and Taxonomic Revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida: Polychaeta). Sabecon Press Science Series, Stuart, Florida." type="book" year="1994">Kirtley (1994)</bibRefCitation>
did not describe the number of opercular paleae of 
<emphasis box="[945,1113,1373,1399]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[945,1110,1373,1399]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Lygdamis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="rayrobertsi">L. rayrobertsi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dos Santos A. S. &amp; Dos Santos Brasil A. C. &amp; Christoffersen M. L." box="[1120,1398,1373,1399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" pagination="125 - 144" refId="ref14997" refString="Dos Santos A. S., Dos Santos Brasil A. C. &amp; Christoffersen M. L. 2014. Sabellaria and Lygdamis (Polychaeta: Sabellariidae) from reefs off northeastern Brazil including a new species of Sabellaria. Zootaxa 3881 (2): 125 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3881.2.2" type="journal article" year="2014">
Dos Santos 
<emphasis box="[1256,1313,1373,1399]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[299,460,1408,1434]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Lygdamis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="rayrobertsi">
<emphasis box="[299,460,1408,1434]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">L. rayrobertsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity box="[477,545,1408,1435]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
long) for 
<collectingCountry box="[662,734,1408,1434]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and describe it with 14 outer paleae, six inner paleae per lobe and opercular papillae of similar size (
<bibRefCitation author="Dos Santos A. S. &amp; Dos Santos Brasil A. C. &amp; Christoffersen M. L." box="[706,983,1443,1469]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" pagination="125 - 144" refId="ref14997" refString="Dos Santos A. S., Dos Santos Brasil A. C. &amp; Christoffersen M. L. 2014. Sabellaria and Lygdamis (Polychaeta: Sabellariidae) from reefs off northeastern Brazil including a new species of Sabellaria. Zootaxa 3881 (2): 125 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3881.2.2" type="journal article" year="2014">
Dos Santos 
<emphasis box="[852,912,1443,1469]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2b), whereas 
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[1202,1299,1443,1469]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Lygdamis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pechi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1202,1299,1443,1469]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">L. pechi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1308,1400,1444,1470]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<quantity box="[199,288,1478,1505]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
long) has only seven outer paleae, four inner paleae per lobe and the first pair of papillae longer than other ones.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1052,1579,1652]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,342,1579,1605]" box="[189,342,1579,1605]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,342,1579,1605]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,1579,1605]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
